===Etymology===
From Welsh [[Lloegr]], the name for the region of present-day England. However, according to [[w:Geoffrey of Monmouth|Geoffrey of Monmouth]], the realm was named after the legendary king [[Locrinus]], the oldest son of Brutus of Troy.

===Alternative spellings===
*[[Loegria]]
*[[Logris]]

